http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/CPI-M-to-go-for-coalition/article13979531.ece

The Communist Party of India (Marxist) is expected to forge a coalition to contest all the 150 divisions in the ensuing GHMC elections.Tammineni Veerabhadram, State secretary president of the party said on Sunday that the party has already formed an alliance with Lok Satta, CPI and Welfare Party of India. “We are also in talks with Aam Admi Party (AAP) and Bahujan Samaj Party (BSP)”, he said. While there are major parties which have money power, people should support parties which offer clean politics, he said.